<h2>Important Notes for October Travel</h2>

<div class="highlight">
<strong>Autumn Foliage Peak</strong><br>
October 12-14 falls during the peak autumn color season around Lake Chuzenji and Yumoto. Buses can be crowded and may experience delays due to traffic congestion, especially on weekends.<br>
<br>
<strong>Recommendations:</strong><br>
• Book earlier departures to avoid crowds<br>
• Allow extra travel time (add 30-60 minutes buffer)<br>
• Consider departing weekdays if possible<br>
• Have backup time plans if buses are full
</div>

<h2>Where to Board the Bus</h2>

<h3>At Tobu Nikko Station</h3>

<p>Exit the station and look for <strong>bus stop platforms 2A, 2B, 2C, or 2D</strong> located directly outside the station building. Signs clearly indicate "Yumoto Onsen" (湯元温泉). Digital displays show upcoming departure times.</p>

<h3>At Yumoto Onsen</h3>

<p>The <strong>Yumoto Onsen Bus Stop</strong> is centrally located near most hotels and hot springs. Look for the covered bus shelter with "Yumoto Onsen" signage. Your hotel can provide specific directions if needed.</p>

<h2>Pro Tips</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>Arrive 10 minutes early</strong> at the bus stop, especially during peak foliage season when buses may fill to capacity.</li>
<li><strong>Keep your phone charged</strong> if using digital passes. Bring a portable battery pack as backup.</li>
<li><strong>Take screenshots</strong> of your bus pass and schedule as offline backup in case of poor signal in the mountains.</li>
<li><strong>Sit on the right side</strong> of the bus going to Yumoto for the best views of Lake Chuzenji and waterfalls.</li>
<li><strong>Consider stopping at Chuzenji Onsen</strong> on your return trip October 14 to visit Kegon Falls before heading to Nikko Station.</li>
<li><strong>Check real-time updates</strong> on the Tobu Bus website or app on the day of travel, as schedules may adjust for traffic or weather.</li>
</ul>

